  <name>ExifGlass</name>
  <summary>EXIF Metadata Viewing Tool</summary>

  <description>
    <p>
      ExifGlass is a fast, open-source EXIF metadata viewer. It reads the technical
      details embedded in your photos - camera settings, lens, exposure, GPS location,
      timestamps, and more - by wrapping the powerful ExifTool by Phil Harvey.
    </p>
    <p>
      Use it standalone via drag-and-drop, the file picker, or a command-line path, or
      plug it into ImageGlass as an integrated tool that live-updates as you navigate
      images. Metadata can be copied to the clipboard or exported to a file.
    </p>
  </description>

